Kim Jong-il's former bodyguard, who protected him during the 1980s, believes that the former dictator's son Kim Jong-un is far more dangerous that the departed 'Dear Leader'. Lee Young-Guk was chosen to protect Kim in 1979, while his father Kim Il Sung still ruled North Korea. Lee said he had to train fanatically to become an elite bodyguard, including having the ability to smash roof tiles with his fists, using martial arts techniques. Scroll down for video Lee Young-Guk spent ten years working as a bodyguard for Kim Jong-Il, left, during the 1980s where he witnessed significant terror among senior officials, he believes the situation is worse under Kim Jong-Un, right
